', '', 'Johnny Green came to Greenwich Village in the late 1960s. He is interviewed by a long-time friend. 

Johnny is from southwest Texas and talks about growing up in a small town. He studied communications and drama in college and then found work in Atlanta as a television producer / director. After several years he joined the local production of “Stomp”, a rock musical that was also a hippie commune. The Public Theater brought the show to New York and the cast and crew lived in Martinson Hall in the East Village. 

Within a year Johnny found an apartment in the West Village where he has lived ever since. He was a salesman at an upscale sex boutique, The Pleasure Chest, until it closed. For nearly 20 years Johnny has been house manager at The Actors Studio. 

Additional controlled search terms: buildings; nightlife; small business. 
Additional key words: Hair (the musical); AIDS. 
', 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/oral-history/audio/Green%2C+Johnny_FINALEDIT.mp3', 0, 'green_johnny.jpg', NULL, NULL, '2014-04-23 19:46:18.268549', '2015-05-21 15:36:36.139233', 1, 0, 1, '');
