', '741 Greenwich Street; 567 Hudson Street; 159 Christopher Street
', '', 'John Joseph Stanley has written hundreds of poems and a manuscript on Thomas Merton. His poems have been published in The Villager and The New Yorker.
', 'John Joseph Stanley has lived in Greenwich Village since 1954. 

By chance he got a job as dishwasher at La Palette restaurant on Bleecker Street and found a place to stay at a nearby rooming house. Later John heard of a vacant apartment on Christopher Street and has lived there ever since. 

He became an actor and appeared in a play with music called Johnny Johnson for nearly 2 years. He then worked at NYU’s student financial aid office. 

John visited Cuba in 1968. While there he observed that the Roman Catholic churches and seminaries were filled. When he returned via Montreal, John noted the falling off of church attendance in Quebec. 
