', '', '', 'Barbara Sherman moved to the Big Apple after nursing school and worked at NYU Medical Center. She has lived in Greenwich Village since 1958 but moved 10 times before settling in an apartment on lower Fifth Avenue. 

Barbara adjusted easily to the neighborhood and her stories run the gamut from exotic pets to the local hangout for car racing enthusiasts, and drug dealers who ruled a nearby street corner. She remembers many popular cafes, bars and restaurants such as The Lion’s Head, 55 Bar and Corner Bistro, and small shops on 8th Street and MacDougal Street. 

In closing, Barbara recalls the West 11th Street townhouse explosion and the September 11 Terrorist Attacks, 2001. 

