', '1982 to 1997
', 'Uncle Charlie''s; The Ninth Circle; Pieces
', '', '', 'Charles Cosentino lives across the river in Jersey City and began spending time in the Village in 1982. He met the interviewer on Facebook. 

Uncle Charlie’s Downtown on Greenwich Avenue was the first gay bar Charles went into and he became a cocktail waiter and occasional DJ there. It was a high-end bar with colored lights and big screens that showed music videos and popular TV shows. But a murder and one of the first terrorist attacks are also part of its history. 

For about 15 years Charles spent most of his time in the Village and knew the gay bars and clubs very well. He also met many friends on the Christopher Street piers. 

Charles has always walked around the neighborhood taking pictures and maintains a popular Facebook page. People are surprised to see how much the area has changed. 

Additional controlled search terms: gay culture; nightlife; social life and customs. 
Additional key words: Lou Katz; pipe bomb explosion; waterfront; The Ninth Circle; Pieces. 
