', '1953 to time of interview
', '53 West 11th Street; 56 West 12th Street; 64 Thompson Street; 304 West 14th Street; 505 LaGuardia Place
', 'Husband, Fred W. McDarrah; sons, Timothy S. McDarrah & Patrick J. McDarrah
', '', 'Gloria McDarrah has lived in the Village since the 1950s. 

Before her husband Fred McDarrah established himself as a photojournalist, he worked as doorman at the Artists’ Club where he had an opportunity to photograph painters Willem de Kooning, Franz Klein and Barnett Newman. Fred’s first book “The Beat Scene” also documented New York School writers such as Allen Ginsberg and Jack Kerouac. He was at the scene after the Weatherman bomb explosion destroyed a townhouse on West 11th Street. 

Once her two sons were in school, Gloria returned to editorial work and then got a job in publicity at the Landmarks Preservation Commission. 

Gloria notes that Greenwich Village is still a wonderful place to live and there are many activities for senior citizens to enjoy, although many small businesses have disappeared. 

Additional controlled search terms: bookstores; buildings; parks; real estate development; Washington Square. 
Additional key words: 10th Street art galleries; Weather Underground; historic preservation; NYU. ', 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/oral-history/audio/McDarrah%2C+Gloria_FINALEDIT.mp3', 0, 'mcdarrah_gloria.jpg', NULL, NULL, '2014-04-23 21:16:07.196031', '2015-05-21 15:46:48.807053', 1, 0, 1, '');
INSERT INTO interviews (id, slug, user_id, interviewer_name, interviewed_at, location, storyteller_name, date_of_birth, place_of_birth, occupations, dates_in_location, other_locations, family_members, notes, summary, url, duration, image, thumb, annotations, created_at, updated_at, neighborhood_id, is_demo, branch_id, transcript_url) VALUES (35, 'rose-hartman-iq8vf2', 1, 'Gemma Haywood', '2014-03-02 00:00:00', 'Home of Storyteller', 'Rose Hartman', '1937-05-16 00:00:00', 'New York City', 'Professional photographer; Author
', '1964 to time of interview
', '88 Charles Street
', '', '', 'Rose Hartman is a Documentary Photographer who has been capturing stylish images for over 34 years. Rose was interviewed by Gemma Haywood on March 2nd 2014, the two had not met before this interview. Rose has been living in Greenwich Village since November 1963. 

Rose has lived through the major changes that have occurred in the village , these include commercialization and the extinction of individual enterprises. She describes this in her interview and also mentions the people responsible for this change and those who have suffered. 
Because of Rose''s occupation she is acquainted with some of the most influential and famous people that Greenwich village has seen. She explains why the village attracts these people and their personalities.
Rose also tells how the village has acted as a sanctuary for her and shares some of her best memories in the West village.  


