', 'St Vincent''s Hospital; 15th Street; East 7th Street; Gay Street; Waverly Place; East 11th Street; West 13th Street
', 'Sisters
', '', 'Carolyn Dickie graduated from nursing school in 1976 and worked at St. Vincent’s Hospital in Greenwich Village for 35 years. She still resides in the neighborhood. 

Carolyn tells many stories about her work at St. Vincent’s. She describes working in the emergency room at the beginning of the AIDS epidemic; riding in the ambulance with the medics; and providing primary medical care to the homeless at walk-in clinics throughout the city. 

Carolyn also talks about camaraderie among her co-workers. After long shifts they would often join in Village nightlife. She is sad to see local small businesses disappear after St. Vincent’s closed in 2010. 

Carolyn recalls other tragic events including the summer of Son of Sam, 9/11, and Hurricane Sandy. 

