', 'Love Greenwich Village; Big Apple greeter; tour guide', 'Carol Kroker came to Greenwich Village in 1967 after graduating from college and found her first apartment on Charlton Street by looking in The Village Voice. She began her career as a social worker and later became a psychotherapist. 

Carol describes 1970s culture and nightlife as diverse and affordable. Greenwich Village was an easy place to make friends with its mix of restaurants, art galleries and theaters. 

Her office is located in the former St. Denis Hotel, built in the 1800’s. She lists famous guests and residents and hopes the building will be landmarked. Carol also notes that 10th Street was once a major shopping district anchored by Wanamaker’s department store. 

Additional controlled search terms: social life and customs; buildings; hotels; small business. 
