', '
', '', 'Ellen Stevenson has been a Greenwich Village resident her entire married life. She is interviewed by a friend.

In 1966 Ellen and her husband discovered they were paying market rate for a rent-controlled apartment. When they lived at 300 Bleecker Street they watched and followed the first Halloween Parade.

Ellen describes the work of the Morton Street Block Association and how it has helped neighbors form a community.

In 1978 developers converted an old factory into residential lofts. Ellen and her husband were the first to buy an apartment. They waited 2 years for the renovations to be completed before moving in and have and lived there for 34 years.
