Readjustment therapist for VA
Mathilda Ziegler online magazine for two years ', '', '', '', 'The BBL has been a very important part of my education as a blind person. I use the BARD book app everyday and believe that books enhance our ability to grow personally and professionally. books in any format, provide the fundamental steps to enrich ourselves and the zorld around us. I started reading at 4, as a challenge due to the fact that I was jealous that my older cousin was being congratulated on how well she was reading. When I lost my sight I  re-learned how to read with my ears and now I cam listen to audiobooks at break neck speed, just like I used to speed read when using my vision. I love to write and one day I hope to publish my poems and perhaps my stories and novels. I love words. Both my parents love to read, my sisters, too.', '', 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/oral-history/audio/Ann+Chiapetta.MP3', 0, 'Ann_and_Verona__1_.jpg', NULL, NULL, '2015-01-12 15:32:02.73949', '2015-02-24 18:07:03.824365', 3, 0, 7, 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/oral-history/transcripts/40056.json');
